# Use Yarn for This Project

- **Package manager**: Use `yarn` for installs and scripts in `Frictionless-Frontend`, not `npm`.
- **Dev server**: Start the Next.js app with `yarn dev`, not `npm run dev`.
- **Starting the server**: When launching the dev server, use this pattern (PowerShell):
  - Free port 3000 if needed, then: `cd "d:\Frictionless\Frictionless-Frontend"; yarn dev`
  - Or: `$conn = Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 3000 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object -First 1; if ($conn) { Stop-Process -Id $conn.OwningProcess -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue }; Set-Location "d:\Frictionless\Frictionless-Frontend"; yarn dev`
